<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17590530-16">
               <interp inst="t17590530-16" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17590530-16" type="year" value="1759"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17590530-16" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17590530"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17590530-16" type="date" value="17590530"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17590530-16-off92-c276" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590530-16-defend309 t17590530-16-off92 t17590530-16-verdict94"></join>
         
               <p>200. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-defend309" type="defendantName">
                     Solomon 
                     Peters 
                  <interp inst="t17590530-16-defend309" type="surname" value="Peters"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-defend309" type="given" value="Solomon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-defend309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17590530-16-off92" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-off92" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-off92" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one bill of exchange; signed 
                     <persName id="t17590530-16-person310">
                        Anthony 
                        Selvin 
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person310" type="surname" value="Selvin"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17590530-16-person310" type="given" value="Anthony"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17590530-16-person310" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  ; value 3 l.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-victim312" type="victimName">
                     Ann 
                     Selby 
                  <interp inst="t17590530-16-victim312" type="surname" value="Selby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-victim312" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-victim312" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590530-16-off92 t17590530-16-victim312"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            ; <rs id="t17590530-16-cd93" type="crimeDate">March 17, 1758</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590530-16-off92 t17590530-16-cd93"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-person313">
                  Ann 
                  Selby 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person313" type="surname" value="Selby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person313" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person313" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had a bill of three pounds, drawn upon Mr 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person314">
                  Robert 
                  Cliff 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person314" type="surname" value="Cliff"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person314" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person314" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Banker, in Lombard-street; which I receiv'd from Mr 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person315">
                  Anthony 
                  Selvin 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person315" type="surname" value="Selvin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person315" type="given" value="Anthony"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person315" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of Durham; he having appointed to lend me 50 l. he order'd me to return this in a post letter, and he would send me 50 l. I put it in a letter before the bill was due, and deliver'd it to the prisoner, to put it in the Post; after that I had word came, it was not receiv'd; I ask'd the prisoner about it; he own'd<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175905300036"></xptr> he had broke open the letter, and taken it out; and had receiv'd the money for it.</p>
               <p>James Quin. (be produc'd the draught) This I receiv'd of the prisoner at the bar, above a year ago; he ow'd me half a guinea, and I gave him the rest of the cash; I paid it to Mrs Macoby, and she gave me 3 l. for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-person316">
                  Ann 
                  Macoby 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person316" type="surname" value="Macoby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person316" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person316" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The draught that Mr Quin deliver'd to me, I kept it 'till due; then I sent my man ( name, 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person317">
                  John 
                  Smith 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person317" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person317" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person317" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ) with it for the cash.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-person318">
                  John 
                  Smith 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person318" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person318" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person318" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I carry'd it to Mr Cliff's, and receiv'd the money for it; here is my name on the back of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-person319">
                  Thomas 
                  Bourne 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person319" type="surname" value="Bourne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person319" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk to Mr Cliff, and Co. I remember particularly well, Mrs Selby bringing this draught to our house, before it was due; and when Mr Smith brought it afterwards; I paid the money and took it.</p>
               <p>The draught read.</p>
               <p>Sir, Pay to Mrs 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person320">
                  Ann 
                  Selby 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person320" type="surname" value="Selby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person320" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person320" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , or order; the sum of 3 l. thirty days after date; and place it to account of your humble servant,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17590530-16-person321">
                  Anthony 
                  Selvin 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person321" type="surname" value="Selvin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person321" type="given" value="Anthony"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person321" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>To Mr 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person322">
                  Robert 
                  Cliff 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person322" type="surname" value="Cliff"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person322" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person322" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; Lombard-street.</p>
               <p>Durham, February 12, 58.</p>
               <p>The prisoner in his defence, said, he was near upon marrying to the prosecutrix then; but it is since broke off; and that she gave him liberty to take the draught and make use of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17590530-16-verdict94" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-verdict94" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.* </p>
               <p>* See him tried before, No. 13. in this Mayoralty. See also No. 6. in Sir 
               <persName id="t17590530-16-person323">
                  Charles 
                  Asgill 
               <interp inst="t17590530-16-person323" type="surname" value="Asgill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person323" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-person323" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's Mayoralty. One for stealing plate, the other for forgery.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17590530-16-punish95" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17590530-16-punish95" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17590530-16-defend309 t17590530-16-punish95"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
